    "media:imagetext": "ARRIVAL OF THE \"CHINA CLIPPER\"'\n5½ DAYS OUT OF THE ORIENT\nAfter a 9,000 mile Trans-Pacific sky voyage\nof three\nThis luxurious lying ship chine\nand\n\"Clipper\"\nis one of a fleet\n\"Philippine\"\n, operated on regular weekly\ntrips between California and the Orient by Pan-\nAmerican\nat the Hawaiian,\nAirways System Wake,\nStops\nare made\nMidway,\nGuam, and\nPhilippine\nIslands,\nen\nroute,\nreducing\nmonth's\nvoyage\nto\nfive\nand\none-half\ndays.\nsea\nThese ships are capable of carrying\nton\nof\nmail\nand\nexpress-\nforty seated\nor eighteen\n-will\naccommodate\nsleeping passengers\non a\nnormal flight.\nThe ships have a\nfuel\ncapacity\nfor a flight of 3,000\nmiles, with a\nhigh speed of 180 miles per hour.\n\"Pictorial Wonderland\"\nPLACE\nONE CENT\nSTAMP\nSTANLEY A. PILTZ COMPANY, SAN FRANCISCO, CALIF.\nHERE\nPOST CARD\n35\n20181121297",
